CJD (new var.) PrP signatures match 970613114830
BSE & CJD (new var.) PrP signatures match (02) 970614153327
CJD-BSE Connection (17) 970108143703

[1
Although the studies so far done on the BSE-nvCJD connection show
astounding similarity in a number of different facets, I believe the
results are being misinterpreted. The fact that nvCJD and BSE prion
proteins act and even respond in identical ways does NOT mean their is
necessarily a causal connection between the two. It simply means the two
agents are extremely similar chemically. In order to adjudge the extent to
which this indicates a causal connection (either implicatively or by a
common cause), we would have to know the false positive rate of such a
comparison. I.e., how many different types of TSE agents are possible. At
the moment, we simply know nvCJD and BSE are a match among the half-dozen
other types studied.
So at present, we know the two agents are remarkably close in chemical
action and structure. Either there are a limited number of subtypes of
prion diseases, or there is a causal connection between the two.
Personally, I find the coincidence of the scrapie pandemic, the BSE
epidemic, the nvCJD disease and the increasing incidence of CJD in the UK
as jointly indicating a causal link among or behind themselves.
I have pieced together the dates of onset of disease from published and
press reports of the 21 nvCJD victims, and performed a simple hazard
function analysis. The results show that, so far as the first 21 cases are
concerned, there is a statistically constant incidence rate of 6.7
(6.3-6.9, 95% confidence) cases per year, with no evidence the case rate is
increasing. The data fit near perfectly (R2=98%) a simple exponential
distribution. The false appearance of an increasing case rate in the news
has been fostered by the clumped release of delayed patient data. (I would
be happy to supply a copy of the report to anyone who may be interested.)
This indicates that, even if nvCJD is being driven by the BSE epidemic, the
incidence of disease is being limited by either a rare combination of
genetic and environmental factors to a near constant and low frequency. It
is also possible that nvCJD is not directly connected to BSE, but is a
naturally occurring variant with action similar to BSE which was discovered
and separately classified by heightened surveillance. It is also possible
that if BSE is driving the nvCJD epidemic, what we have seen so far is a
self-limiting low incubation period type, and latter and larger pulses with
increasing rates will appear after a longer incubation period.
[Robert raises some interesting points but clearly the new research pushes
the BSE & nvCJD causal football down the field a great deal. Analysis and
modelling of the epidemic curve will certainly be important for monitoring
the epidemic. The work done on the predictive modelling for the BSE
epidemic by John Wilesmith's group has really been valuable in
understanding where things are and what should be done. - Mod. pc
